==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|nl}}, named after the island [[Curaçao]], one of the [[Dutch Antilles]], itself named after the {{etyl|pt}} word {{term|curação||medical cure|lang=pt}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|curatio||cure|lang=la}}, from {{term|curare||to cure|lang=la}}, from {{term|cura||care, cure|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
{{rfp}} [[IPA]]: [[UK]] /kjuːrə.səʊ/ [[US]] /kjuːrəˈsoʊ/

===Noun===
{{en-noun|curaçaos|-}}

# A [[liqueur]], made from [[eau-de-vie]], [[sugar]] and, as [[flavor]], dried [[peel]] of sweet and sour [[orange]]s.

